    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Metro Briefing | New Jersey: Trenton: Malpractice Bill Advances</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Laura Mansnerus (NYT); Compiled by Anthony Ramirez</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Mansnerus, Laura</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New Jersey State Senate approves legislation overhauling medical malpractice laws; establishes fund to help pay malpractice insurance premiums for doctors in high risk fields; does not cap damage awards, but gives judges more authority to limit them (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The State Senate approved legislation yesterday overhauling medical malpractice laws, the subject of strikes and demonstrations last year by doctors across the state. The 22-to-15 vote followed party lines. The measure establishes a fund to help pay malpractice insurance premiums for doctors in high-risk specialties like obstetrics and neurosurgery. It does not cap damages awards, as Republicans had wanted, but gives judges more authority to limit them. The General Assembly, which has approved a similar bill, will now receive the Senate version.</p>
        <p>Laura Mansnerus (NYT)</p>
      </block>
